Have you ever felt paralyzed by a decision you had to make?

Feeling unsure is common unless we align ourselves with God.

This is what Paul is referring to in 1 Corinthians 2:15-16: "The person with the Spirit makes judgments about all things, but such a person is not subject to merely human judgments, for, 'Who has known the mind of the Lord so as to instruct him?' But we have the mind of Christ."

Paul says that the Spirit of God will reveal to us those things that have been freely given to us. The implied benefit is that we can make the right decisions in life by tapping into the mind of Christ. I think you would have to agree that this is pretty awesome!

The next time you have to make a big decision, will you have the mind of Christ?

Proverbs 3:5 tells us, “Trust in the Lord with all your heart, and lean not on your own understanding; in all your ways acknowledge Him, and He shall direct your paths.”
 
I know that’s not always easy to do. But “all your ways” means all your ways. 

That means you have to acknowledge that you don’t have all the answers. 

That means that you’re going to have to trust Him to lead you in life. 

That means that you can’t try to do anything based on your past victories. Oftentimes, the enemy is already wise to them, and he’s already changed strategies. And only God knows that.

#GoodFather #KingdomLiving #Faith

That's how it is with God's promises—He gave you an inheritance of His estate, legally. All you have to do is believe in it.

It's done. You have access to His rest, provision, and healing.

#Faith #GoodFather #UnfinishedBusiness

When was the last time you actually stopped and considered the people around you and what they might be going through right now?

When was the last time you looked people in the eye and smiled as you passed them?

When was the last time you had a real conversation with the person waiting on your table at a restaurant?

When was the last time you asked your coworker how they’re doing and really listened to his or her answer?

See, the thing is, you can be around people all of the time, but if you’re not careful, you will never actually see them.

But God sees them. He knows everything about them.

And He needs your help to reach them.

Even if it’s only one person at a time.

#GoodFather #KingdomLiving #Faith

I thank God for dreams and visions.

I think part of the answer is that we are all so busy, and when we're quiet, He can catch our attention. Or it may be because we are in such a state of confusion or circumstances are such that it is hard to hear God's voice. Either way, the Holy Spirit is just trying to give you a message.

As we go into the new year, I encourage you to spend time in silence and prayer, taking note of the visions and dreams God could be planting.

Ask God to guide you in making your goals and vision. He has the best plan for you!

#Purpose #Faith #NewYears2023

He healed many people during his ministry, but His larger purpose was to liberate humanity from sin and share the transformative power of God's Kingdom with everyone. He didn't let those great meetings of healing and exorcizing demons keep Him from His purpose.

Focus on the greater plan God has for you—that's the greatest thing you can do.

There's nothing YOU can do that will change the fact that everyone is headed for hell.

The Good News is you don't have to do anything to be saved from that horrible destination. Jesus did it all for us. We simply need to believe in our hearts that He is who He said He is and confess it with our mouths.

Acts 2:21 says, "And everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved."

When you call on the name of Jesus, you'll be saved from hell. You see, Jesus was God’s rescue plan to bring His creation back into His Kingdom, where He had originally designed man to live. Stop believing that if you're just "good enough," you'll make it to heaven. It's about your faith, not about your works.
